Lawrence's Review of TruGlo Tritium Pistol Night Sight


        The optics of the sights themselves are superb.The quality and durability are terrible. The customer service is yet to be seen. I know that the covers on what appeared to be a fully enclosed metal piece that sits in front of the fiber optic tube, that also enclosed the night sight materials, fell out of the sights in less than two hundred rounds. They required that I mail the slide back to them ,this cost an additional $29 dollar experience. Adding obviously $29 to the already high purchase price. The customer service department told me that they have no way to sight in the sights. I will have to bring it to a gun Smith upon it's return. Although Trijicon sights are not as bright, they are much more durable.
            



Pros:

Excellent optics and night lumination



Cons:

They apparently fall apart in in than 200 rounds ,are not worth
They apparently fall apart in less than 200 rounds



Best Used for:

Ovoid these sights and get something reliable.






 Would Recommend: 
                No            



