Tru-Glo tritium sights








        by
                                Ralph,
                                    from CA, United States
                Written on January 6, 2015
    



        I fitted these myself to my Glock 30.  This job requires a special thinwall socket to remove the tiny hex head bolt and these are available on the Net for about $9 ppd.
The rear sight was removed with a brass punch, the slide held between two pieces of wood in my vise.

Once fitted, I checked the sights for night visibility and they are very clearly visible in total darkness.  I like them and they are a valuable addition to my home defense weapon.    




Would recommend:  Yes 

