Great Night Sights








        by
                                    

                        Legacy Reviewer,
                            Verified Owner
                            from OR, United States
                Written on August 27, 2013
    



        I bought these sights to replace the dim, beat-up factory Meprolight sights on my Kimber CDP. The TruGlos installed with little fuss and just minor filing on the rear dovetail. The finish is fine and the tritium is really bright (brighter than AmeriGlo and Trijicon sights that I have). The only note is that these sights do look substantially more "angular" or "tough" than the original (rounded) factory sights. That may or may not be a good thing to you.
Pros: Bright, tough, great price
Cons: Required some fitting    




Would recommend:  Yes 

